A matrix in Java is a 2D array (array of arrays).

matrix.length gives the number of rows.
matrix[0].length gives the number of columns in the first row.

Example:

int[][] matrix = {
    {1, 2, 3},
    {4, 5, 6},
    {7, 8, 9}
};

System.out.println(matrix.length);      // 3 Rows
System.out.println(matrix[0].length);   // 3 Columns

Here, the matrix has 3 rows and 3 columns, so matrix.length = 3 and matrix[0].length = 3.